It's part of the java.util package and can be used to sort both primitive and object arrays. 
Different methods in Arrays class are
	- Arrays.sort()
	- Arrays.equals()
	- Arrays.fill()
	- Arrays.asList()
	- Arrays.copyOf()
	- Arrays.toString()
The Arrays.sort() method in Java is a powerful and efficient way to sort arrays. 
Depending on the type of array, Arrays.sort() uses different sorting algorithms optimized for performance,like QuickSort, MergeSort, or TimSort.